---
description: Rules for live game updates, clutch alerts, and realtime stability.
globs:
  - client/src/lib/useLiveScores.ts
  - client/src/lib/useLiveGameCenter.ts
  - client/src/lib/liveGameCenter.ts
  - client/src/components/LiveGameCenter.tsx
  - api/push-notify.ts
---

- Prefer resilient data fallbacks when ESPN payloads omit fields.
- Keep polling idempotent and bounded; avoid duplicate notification sends.
- Use one-time clutch alert semantics per game id.
- Never expose service role secrets in client code.
- Keep live UI non-blocking: load partial panels even when one subfeed fails.
- Preserve existing visual language (`glass-card`, `section-label`, accent blue/emerald/rose).
